fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.core

Class DefaultNegativeConstraint

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.core.DefaultRule
      • fr.lirmm.graphik.graal.core.DefaultNegativeConstraint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NegativeConstraint, Rule, AppendableToStringBuilder, Comparable<Rule>

    public class DefaultNegativeConstraint
extends DefaultRule
implements NegativeConstraint
    A negative constraint prevents to have some set of atoms. Its logical representation is: "¬animal(X) ∧ ¬plant(X)".
    The NegativeConstraint Class represent negative constraint by a rule that produce the Bottom atom if the specified atom set is met.
    Author:
    Clément Sipieter (INRIA) <clement@6pi.fr>
